{
  "schema": "anip-starter-template/v0",
  "anipSpecVersion": "anip/0.24",
  "id": "notion-fronting-starter",
  "kind": "fronting_starter",
  "projectType": "governed_service_project",
  "title": "Notion Fronting Starter",
  "summary": "Template-suggested Notion API/MCP fronting structure with reviewed capability candidates.",
  "description": "Starts a governed Notion fronting project from sample API/MCP seams. Use only when you want template-suggested data that must be reviewed against your real Notion integration.",
  "domain": "notion",
  "recommendedBrief": "Create a governed ANIP fronting layer for Notion. Expose selected capabilities for bounded workspace search, database query context, page creation preparation, page update preparation, and comment preparation. Raw Notion tools should not be exposed directly to agents. Reads must preserve actor-visible scope. Write-adjacent operations must prepare previews, require explicit approval before execution, audit the request, and clarify missing required inputs instead of guessing.",
  "documents": [
    {
      "idSuffix": "template-fronting-intent",
      "title": "Notion fronting intent",
      "kind": "business_intent",
      "filename": "notion-fronting-intent.md",
      "content": "# Notion Governed Fronting Intent\n\n> Imported from starter template `notion-fronting-starter`. Treat this as draft guidance, not discovered truth.\n\nExpose a small governed Notion capability surface in front of native API or MCP-backed operations.\n\n## Template-suggested capabilities\n- notion.workspace.search_context: Search bounded Notion pages and databases without exposing raw workspace tools.\n- notion.database.query_context: Query a bounded Notion database view with declared filters and return summarized context.\n- notion.page.create.prepare: Prepare a Notion page creation preview under an explicit parent before creating anything.\n- notion.page.update.prepare: Prepare a Notion page update preview for an explicit page without applying the update.\n- notion.comment.prepare: Prepare a Notion page comment from supplied context without posting it.\n\n## Governance posture\n- Raw Notion tools are not exposed directly to agents.\n- Read capabilities return bounded actor-visible context.\n- Write-adjacent capabilities prepare previews and require explicit approval before execution.\n- Missing required inputs trigger clarification instead of guessing."
    },
    {
      "idSuffix": "template-integration-evidence",
      "title": "Notion integration evidence",
      "kind": "api_docs",
      "filename": "notion-integration-evidence.template.md",
      "content": "# Notion Integration Evidence Template\n\n> Imported from starter template `notion-fronting-starter`. Verify every operation against your chosen Notion API/MCP source before locking.\n\nNative API connection: https://api.notion.com/v1\nMCP connection: NOTION_MCP_ENDPOINT\n\n## Template-suggested backend operations\n- notion.api.workspace_search_context: POST /search\n- notion.mcp.workspace_search_context: MCP tool workspace_search_context\n- notion.api.database_query_context: POST /databases/{database_id}/query\n- notion.mcp.database_query_context: MCP tool database_query_context\n- notion.api.page_create_prepare: POST /pages\n- notion.mcp.page_create_prepare: MCP tool page_create_prepare\n- notion.api.page_update_prepare: PATCH /pages/{page_id}\n- notion.mcp.page_update_prepare: MCP tool page_update_prepare\n- notion.api.comment_prepare: POST /comments\n- notion.mcp.comment_prepare: MCP tool comment_prepare\n\n## Secret posture\n- Studio stores secret references only; project exports must not contain tokens.\n- Teams can implement either native API or MCP backend seams behind the same governed ANIP contract."
    }
  ],
